Document: WebRTCDataChannel
Path: godot/classes/class_webrtcdatachannel.rst
Summary: Provides an interface for sending and receiving data over a WebRTC connection.

WebRTCDataChannel

Inherits: Object < Object

This class represents a WebRTC Data Channel, which is used for sending and receiving arbitrary data between peers. It can be used for real-time communication of any kind of data, such as game state, chat messages, or sensor data.

The Data Channel is established over an existing WebRTC peer connection. Once established, it provides a reliable or unreliable transport for data.

Key Rule: The WebRTCDataChannel can only be created after a WebRTC connection has been established.

Key Rule: Data channels can be configured to be ordered or unordered, and reliable or unreliable.

Key Rule: The state of the data channel can be monitored to determine when it is ready for use.

Methods:
close() → void
Closes the data channel.

create_offer() → Error
Creates an offer to establish a data channel.

get_state() → int
Returns the current state of the data channel.

is_datachannel_ready() → bool
Checks if the data channel is ready to send data.

send_bytes(data: PackedByteArray) → Error
Sends binary data over the data channel.

send_mode_is_reliable() → bool
Returns true if the data channel is configured for reliable transfer.

send_string(data: String) → Error
Sends string data over the data channel.

Signals:
closed → void
Emitted when the data channel is closed.

error → void
Emitted when an error occurs with the data channel.

message_from(message: Variant) → void
Emitted when a message is received from the peer.

sctp_connected → void
Emitted when the SCTP connection is established.

state_changed → void
Emitted when the state of the data channel changes.

Enums:
State:
STATE_CONNECTING: 0
STATE_OPEN: 1
STATE_CLOSING: 2
STATE_CLOSED: 3
