Document: WebRTCDataChannel
Path: godot/classes/class_webrtcdatachannel.rst
Summary: This section details the methods and enumerations available for the WebRTCDataChannel class in Godot.

Methods
Method: close()
Closes the data channel.

Method: get_buffered_amount() → int
Returns the number of bytes of data that has been sent but not yet acknowledged by the remote peer.

Method: get_id() → int
Returns the unique ID of this data channel.

Method: get_label() → String
Returns the label of this data channel.

Method: get_max_packet_life_time() → int
Returns the maximum amount of time in milliseconds that a packet will be kept if it's not acknowledged by the remote peer.

Method: get_max_retransmits() → int
Returns the maximum number of retransmits that will be attempted for a packet if it's not acknowledged by the remote peer.

Method: get_protocol() → String
Returns the sub-protocol used by this data channel.

Method: get_ready_state() → ChannelState
Returns the current state of the data channel.

Method: is_negotiated() → bool
Returns true if this data channel was created by the user, false if it was created automatically by WebRTC.

Method: is_ordered() → bool
Returns true if this data channel guarantees in-order delivery of messages.

Method: poll() → Error
Polls the data channel for incoming data and events.

Method: was_string_packet() → bool
Returns true if the last packet received was a string, false if it was binary.

Enumerations
enum WriteMode:
WRITE_MODE_TEXT = 0: Tells the channel to send data over this channel as text. An external peer (non-Godot) would receive this as a string.
WRITE_MODE_BINARY = 1: Tells the channel to send data over this channel as binary. An external peer (non-Godot) would receive this as array buffer or blob.

enum ChannelState:
STATE_CONNECTING = 0: The channel was created, but it's still trying to connect.
STATE_OPEN = 1: The channel is currently open, and data can flow over it.
STATE_CLOSING = 2: The channel is being closed, no new messages will be accepted, but those already in queue will be flushed.
STATE_CLOSED = 3: The channel was closed, or connection failed.
